        Isabel Wilkerson's <em>The Warmth of Other Suns</em> (2010) is the definitive account of the Great Migration — built from 15 years of research and 1,200 interviews, and told through the lives of three individuals who made the journey. It won the National Book Critics Circle Award. It is the starting point for anyone who wants to understand this period in depth.
      </p>
